  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "At the moment, all our `console.sol` calls are simply logged with `console.log`. This functionality cannot be disabled nor configured.\r\n\r\nMy proposal is to allow this in the config:\r\n\r\n```\r\nnetworks: {\r\n  hardhat: {\r\n    consoleLog: true | false | ConsoleLogHandler\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhere `true` is the default, `false` means disabled, and `ConsoleLogHandler` is something like:\r\n\r\n```\r\ntype ConsoleLogHandler = (args: any[]) => void\r\n```\r\n\r\nI also considered doing `(...args: any[])`, but that's less future proof. For example, maybe later we want to add the raw calldata received by the `console.sol` address as a second parameter.",
  "closed_by": null,
